# Frontend Rules

## 1. File Structure

### 1.1 Module folder structure
Every feature module SHOULD follow this structure.

```
modules/
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ <feature>/
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ index.ts                  barrel ‚Äî re-exports components, api, queries, store, types, utils (see ¬ß1.5)
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <feature>.api.ts          raw axios functions ‚Äî no hooks, no state
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <feature>.store.ts        store management (optional)
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <feature>.queries.ts      TanStack Query hooks only
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <feature>.types.ts        (optional) UI-only types used in 2+ files ‚Äî see ¬ß10.3‚Äì10.4; do not add when scaffolding a module
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <feature>.utils.ts       (optional) module-only helpers
    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ components/               components used ONLY by this module
        ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ index.ts              barrel ‚Äî re-export all public components (and optional shared hooks)
        ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ FeatureCard.tsx
        ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ FeatureForm.tsx
        ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ FeatureList.tsx
```

Notes:
- Do **not** create `<feature>.types.ts` when starting a new module. Add it only when a UI-only type is shared across **more than one** component or file (see ¬ß10.4).
- Import domain/API types from `@task-forge/shared/types` **directly** in the file that needs them ‚Äî never re-export shared types through `<feature>.types.ts`.

### 1.2 Global component folders (`src/components/`)

The entire **`apps/frontend/src/components/`** tree is for **app-wide UI and common components** (primitives, shell, cross-feature widgets). Feature-only UI stays in **`modules/<feature>/components/`** (see ¬ß1.1).

```
src/components/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ index.ts          barrel ‚Äî re-export the public app-wide API (see below), including `ui/` primitives when desired
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ ui/               shadcn primitives ‚Äî NEVER edit manually
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ layout/           app shell ‚Äî Header, Sidebar, PageWrapper, etc.
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ shared/           legacy only ‚Äî do NOT add new files here (see notes)
```

**Barrel (`src/components/index.ts`)**

- Maintain **`index.ts`** at **`src/components/`** and export anything meant for cross-app import (e.g. layout pieces, `ErrorBoundary`, `LoadingSpinner`, `AppErrorView`).
- Prefer **`import { ‚Ä¶ } from '@/components'`** (or `@/components/index`) for those symbols instead of deep paths, when the barrel exports them.
- When the project chooses a single import surface, it is acceptable to barrel-export `ui/` primitives from **`src/components/index.ts`** and import them via **`@/components`**.
- Keep direct imports from **`@/components/ui/...`** valid for existing code and incremental migration.

**Where to add new common components**

- Add new files as **`src/components/<Name>.tsx`** (PascalCase, matches ¬ß2.1) or, if several files belong together, **`src/components/<feature>/`** (e.g. small group of colocated files) ‚Äî **not** under **`src/components/shared/`**.
- **`src/components/shared/`** is **legacy / frozen**: **do not add new files** there; migrate existing pieces out over time when you touch them.

Rule: if a component is used by only one module ‚Äî it lives in `modules/<feature>/components/`.
If used by two or more modules ‚Äî it lives under **`src/components/`** (outside `shared/` for new work) and should be exported from **`src/components/index.ts`** when it is part of the public surface.

### 1.3 App Router structure
```
src/app/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ layout.tsx                    root layout ‚Äî Providers wrapper only
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ page.tsx                      redirects to /dashboard or /login
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ (auth)/
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ login/page.tsx
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ register/page.tsx
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ (portal)/
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ layout.tsx                portal shell with sidebar + header
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ dashboard/page.tsx
    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ properties/
        ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ page.tsx              list view
        ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ [id]/page.tsx         detail/edit view
```

Only add a new store file if the state is truly global (needed in 3+ unrelated components).
Otherwise use TanStack Query server state or local React state.

### 1.4 Lib folder
```
src/lib/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ axios.ts          axios instance with baseURL + auth interceptors
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ queryClient.ts    TanStack Query client config
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ utils.ts          cn() helper from shadcn ‚Äî utility functions only
```

### 1.5 Module barrel exports (`index.ts`)

Every feature module **SHOULD** use two barrel files so consumers can import from `@/modules/<feature>` and `@/modules/<feature>/components` without deep file paths.

**`modules/<feature>/components/index.ts`**

- Re-export **all public components** in that folder using **`export { default as ComponentName } from './ComponentName'`** (see ¬ß5.2) so consumers get stable named imports from the barrel.
- Optionally re-export co-located **hooks** (e.g. `*.hook.ts`) if they are imported from outside `components/` (e.g. from `app/`). Hooks used only by a single component do not need a barrel export.
- Do **not** re-export shadcn `ui/` primitives from here.

Example (components use default export per ¬ß5.1‚Äì5.2):

```ts
export { default as FeatureCard } from './FeatureCard'
export { default as FeatureForm } from './FeatureForm'
```

**`modules/<feature>/index.ts`**

- Re-export **everything** intended as the module‚Äôs public API, typically:
  - `export * from './components'` (or explicit re-exports from `./components` if you need to avoid name clashes)
  - `<feature>.api.ts` ‚Äî export functions and any types that belong in the API layer
  - `<feature>.queries.ts` ‚Äî export hooks and exported query keys (e.g. `AUTH_KEYS`)
  - Optional: `<feature>.store.ts`, `<feature>.types.ts` (UI-only, multi-file ‚Äî ¬ß10.4), `<feature>.utils.ts` when the module defines them
- App Router pages and other modules should prefer `import { ‚Ä¶ } from '@/modules/<feature>'` when pulling module API, queries, or components.

**Constraints**

- Avoid circular imports: the module `index.ts` must not create cycles (e.g. `queries` importing from `index`); keep barrels as pure re-exports where possible.
- If a symbol is internal to the module, do **not** add it to the barrels.

