## 6. Form Rules

### 6.1 Always use React Hook Form + Zod

### 6.2 For form handle logic keep it in separate file like taskForm.hook.ts
In this file handle form initial value declaration, schema validation and submit logic.
If required pass params.

### 6.3 Always use shadcn Form components

### 6.4 Always handle loading and error states in forms
---

## 7. State Management Rules

### 7.1 Server state ‚Äî always TanStack Query
Any data that comes from the API is server state. Use TanStack Query.
Never put API data into Zustand.

### 7.2 Client state ‚Äî Zustand for global, useState for local

### 7.3 Auth store rules
The auth store is the only Zustand store that persists to localStorage.
Never store sensitive data beyond token and basic user info.

---

## 8. Component State Management
Always create component folder inside `/module/<feature>/component` for loading, error and empty-data state
and create index.tsx file for main component.
1. Loading State - `<feature>-loading-skeleton.tsx`
2. Error State - `<feature>-error.tsx`
3. Empty Data State - `<feature>-empty-data.tsx`
4. Component with data - `<feature>-index.tsx` handle 1,2,3 state in this file.

---

### 9 Use ErrorBoundary for unexpected errors
Wrap page-level components in **`ErrorBoundary`** from the app components barrel when exported, e.g. **`import { ErrorBoundary } from '@/components'`**, otherwise **`@/components/shared/ErrorBoundary`** until the barrel re-exports it.

```tsx
// (portal)/tasks/page.tsx
import { ErrorBoundary } from '@/components'

export default function PropertiesPage() {
  return (
    <ErrorBoundary>
      <TaskList />
    </ErrorBoundary>
  )
}
```

